fileengine-core (2.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * ACL model: read-by-default with access-time parent-container traversal.
  * New "everyone" (OTHER) principal alias for clear deny-to-all rules.
  * New CULL_VERSIONS permission; PurgeOldVersions now requires it instead of
    WRITE (breaking change for existing purge callers).

 -- FileEngine Team <maintainer@fileengine.example.com>  Fri, 26 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

fileengine-core (1.0.0-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Split into four binary packages: fileengine-libs, fileengine-server,
    fileengine-server-dev, fileengine-cli.
  * libfileengine_core.so moves to fileengine-libs so CLI and server can
    install independently; both depend on it via fileengine-libs.
  * fileengine-server now owns the systemd unit, default config, logrotate
    rule, and the fileengine system user/group.
  * fileengine-cli is now a minimal package — just the binary.

 -- FileEngine Team <maintainer@fileengine.example.com>  Wed, 17 Jun 2026 22:00:00 +0000

fileengine-core (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial release of FileEngine Core
  * Implements distributed virtual filesystem with horizontal scaling
  * Supports hybrid cloud/on-premises deployment
  * Includes encryption and compression support
  * Provides S3/MinIO integration

 -- FileEngine Team <maintainer@fileengine.example.com>  Wed, 07 Jan 2026 17:00:00 +0000